{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q841105]] Wikidata name: 28th day of the 11th month in the Chinese calendar [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 08:37, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{Not to be confused with|November 28|qq=November 28}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十一月廿八|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 11월 28일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar November|qq=}} '''November 28''' is the 28th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}} – the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} and its day is {{ill|Tomobiki|qid=Q96759840}}{{efn|ja|友引|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q9418169}}{{efn|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomobiki|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q9418169}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Jōkyō|Tenkyō]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1685|1685]] [[:en:January 3|January 3]]) – [[:en:Shibukawa Shunkai|Shibukawa Harumi]] revised the old Senmyō calendar into the Yamato calendar (later known as the [[:en:Jōkyō|Tenkyō]] calendar). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1872|1872]] [[:en:December 28|December 28]]) – The customs offices at Nagasaki, Yokohama, and Hakodate were renamed as customs. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] 1872nd year 12月28日) – A decree for universal conscription was issued, prompting uprisings in various regions.
== Births == * [[:en:Keiō|Keiō]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1866|1866]] [[:en:August 19|August 19]]) – [[中村不折]], a Western-style painter and calligrapher (died [[:en:1943|1943]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Empress Jitō|Empress Jitō]] 10th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:696|696]] [[:en:August 13|August 13]]) – [[高市皇子]], a prince of Emperor Tenmu (born ~654?). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 7th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1824|1824]] [[:en:August 4|August 4]]) – [[Maeda Seihiro]], 12th lord of the Kaga Domain (born [[:en:1782|1782]]).
